social_posts.post_text: My chosen fam in this chaotic city 💕
Giddy up it’s about to be a wild few months 🌹
2022 the year I grew my wings 🦋
Sydney ❤️
“It’s pronounced Mel-bin”
Soaking up all things Aus 🐨🦘

My dad is my hero, 
He’s 65 today. He has shown me every corner of the world, and to never stop exploring. I inherited his resilience and learnt that sacrifice and stubbornness when harnessed correctly can help you achieve exactly what you want. He taught me about music, art, exploring different cuisines - and of course that Chelsea FC is the superior football club. He only encouraged me when I decided to move across the globe and our coffee date catch ups are now some of my favourite days. He is a cancer survivor (cancer free since 2016!!), and we conquered a mountain together after his hip replacement. He loves my mum, my brother and I more than anything.

It’s an honour to be his daughter, to share each others dreams, and to have lived and worked in our shared passions of music, and track and field. 

I can’t wait to see him thrive and share in all the amazing new chapters of life to come ❤️

Happy birthday Stevie wonder boy - you’re the greatest to ever do it!
Summer blues 💙
We have some news 💕🤰🏻

I’m finding both peace and power within this pregnancy and loving every second as I’m being shaped into the newest version of myself - mum (or mom?) 

Thank you so so so much for the kind words, well wishes, love, and hilarious reactions. Every moment, every little kick, and every tiny milestone with bump so far has been so precious and we will hold the memories close to our hearts forever ❤️

Summer snaps from the bump bank 🤰🏻🌞 

Having fun getting everything ready for Teeny’s arrival - parents pls comment any must haves

Bursting (literally) with love after yesterdays baby shower & birthday celebration 🧚🏼‍♀️🫧🫶✨💕 baby girl and I are so blessed to have such incredible people in our lives. 

Thank u to my amazing friends for making the day so fun and ofc to mumma Jules, I hope I can make every day of her life as special as you’ve made mine 🥲❤️
Game face ready 😤😤

🚨Sydney & Shire based mums to be🚨 I cannot suggest attending @onemamamidwife ‘s antenatal childbirth education classes enough! After a few recommendations from both my midwife and friends, I’m so glad that I went and soaked up all her knowledge that left me feeling prepared, excited, and confident for everything birth + babies! 👶

As a first time mum I’ve been overwhelmed with the amount of information and opinions out there and was reassured to have Loz who is both a NSW private midwife and mama herself sharing all her tips, tricks and experience on what to expect. 

The class was fun and interactive and we were even gifted amazing goodie bag at the end for us all to take home 🤰🏻🍼

In summary - go see @onemamamidwife , she’s awesome 🫶🥰🏥

We didn’t get around to an official maternity shoot. The timing didn’t work out, or it didn’t feel right. If I’m being honest I’m not one to really enjoy an “official shoot” at the best of times. What DID feel right tho, was a day at the beach with my best mate (@amypejkovic), a walk along the rock pools, a coffee in hand and her candidly testing out her new camera. And this was the result 📸🤰🏻I’m so grateful for these pics 💕

Dreamt of days like this 💜
Baby love is the best
Not even 8 weeks old and Vibelet is already slaying 🫡 #imamom

Feeling very proud of myself as I leave the all consuming “4th trimester”. I’ve always had a weird relationship with change, and boy did the last 12 weeks consist of an enormous amount of it. Classified as a time of great physical and emotional change as you heal from birth, adjust to your new life as a mum, and baby adjusts to life outside of the womb. The first 12 weeks with baby Vi was as amazing as it was overwhelming and if she’s anything like me I know the chaos won’t slow down anytime soon. The next chapter for us will be fun as she continues to grow and show her personality, and exciting for me as I try working out again (martial arts and Pilates ??), and get back to travelling. 
So grateful for my happy baby 💜
POV you’re FaceTiming us 📞💜
putting the pieces together with puzzles, pilates, podcasts & plenty of time with friends (and bevs) 🧩
My teeny beach babe and me ⛱️
A very wholesome carrousel 💜
A weekend down the coast with my violet 🌥️
Cha cha real smooth 💃🏻❤️
the most transformative year yet ❤️

OLYMPIAN 💫
